com.jauntium

Class Form

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jauntium.Form

  • public class Form
extends Object
    A utility component that makes it easy fill-out the fields of a particular HTML form; convenience methods allow for reading/setting input fields (eg textfields, dropdown menus, checkboxes, etc) on the basis of their labels (ie the adjacent text) or by applying a sequence of inputs.

      • apply

        public Form apply(Object... args)
           throws JauntiumException
        Applies the specified parameters in succession to the form's editable (ie, visible and non-disabled) inputs, starting from the input after the most recently edited input, or starting from the first input, if the form has not yet been edited.
        Parameters:
        args - an arg of type String will populate a textfield/textarea/passwordField OR select the matching menuItem in a dropdown menu OR select the matching right-side label of a radiobutton (unless the string is "\t", in which case it will skip to the next form component); a Boolean param will check/uncheck a checkbox; any other type of param will be treated as a String by calling its toString() method; If number of args exceeds the number of form controls, the extra arguments are ignored.
        Throws:
        JauntiumException

      • submit

        public Document submit(String buttonText)
                throws NotFound
        Submits the the form by clicking the first submit button who's value (ie, text label) matches the specified (case-insensitive) buttonText and throws a NotFound Exception if it does not exist.
        Returns:
        Document corresponding to the page retrieved after submitting the form.
        Throws:
        NotFound
